academicProgress: During the academic year, the college successfully introduced new academic programs aligned with national and international standards. Curriculum revision was undertaken to integrate modern pedagogical approaches and outcome-based learning practices. Continuous assessment and remedial classes were implemented to improve student performance and overall results. Faculty development workshops and training sessions were also conducted to enhance teaching quality and academic excellence.
researchProgress: The college has actively promoted a research-driven academic culture. Several faculty- and student-led research projects were completed during the year, some of which were published in reputed journals. The college hosted national-level seminars and conferences to foster academic exchange and innovation. Initiatives for establishing research collaborations and pursuing research grants were also strengthened, further encouraging innovation and interdisciplinary research activities.
adminProgress: Administrative processes were streamlined through digitalization and policy refinement. The college formed new committees to enhance transparency, accountability, and participatory decision-making. Regular meetings and audits ensured effective monitoring of institutional activities. Efforts were made to improve inter-departmental coordination and communication, leading to better governance and operational efficiency.
qualityProgress: The college continued to prioritize quality assurance through active engagement with QAAC guidelines. Internal Quality Assurance mechanisms were strengthened, and feedback systems for students, faculty, and stakeholders were effectively implemented. Periodic evaluations and peer reviews were carried out to maintain high academic and institutional standards. Quality enhancement training sessions were also organized to ensure continuous improvement in teaching, learning, and administration.
majorChallenges: The college encountered challenges such as resource limitations, increasing student enrollment without proportional infrastructure expansion, and delays in policy approvals. Recruitment of qualified faculty in specialized disciplines and adapting to rapid technological changes also remained key concerns. Despite these issues, the college managed to sustain academic quality and operational stability through effective planning and teamwork.
nextYearPlan: The college aims to expand research and innovation activities, strengthen digital learning infrastructure, and establish stronger industry-academic partnerships. Plans include launching new skill-oriented programs, upgrading laboratories and libraries, and implementing advanced student support systems.
